    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nSetting colorscheme from init.vim broke after updating to NeoVim v0.9.0.\r\n\r\nI have a custom colorscheme in ./config/nvim/colors/colors.vim\r\nIn my config file at ./config/nvim/init.vim I set the colorscheme with `colorscheme colors`\r\n\r\nBut yesterday after NeoVim update this stopped working.\r\nNow for it to work I have to call `:colorscheme colors` manually after starting NeoVim.\r\n\r\nSeems like only `hi clear` statements are affected.\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nHave this as `./config/nvim/init.vim`:\r\n\r\n    filetype plugin indent on\r\n\r\n    syntax enable\r\n    colorscheme colors\r\n\r\nHave this as `./config/nvim/colors/colors.vim`:\r\n\r\n    hi clear\r\n\r\n    if exists('syntax_on')\r\n      syntax reset\r\n    endif\r\n\r\n    syntax enable\r\n    set background=dark\r\n\r\n    hi clear Number\r\n    hi clear Character\r\n    hi clear Statement\r\n    hi clear Type\r\n    hi clear Function\r\n    hi clear PreProc\r\n    hi clear Special\r\n    hi clear Identifier\r\n    hi clear Constant\r\n    hi clear Boolean\r\n    hi clear String\r\n    hi clear Delimiter\r\n    hi clear Conceal\r\n    hi clear Directory\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\n`hi clear` statements are applied after starting NeoVim, without the need to call the colorscheme manually.\r\n\r\nSeems like the was the behaviour in the previous version of NeoVim.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\n0.9.0 Release\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nno, vim 9.0.270\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nmacOS 13.3\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nApple terminal 2.13; GNU screen 4.09.00\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nscreen-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nmacports",
